::Shadow Wing::

She was glad that someone was able to reply to her transmission and 
go to help the bot.  She was wasn't glad that Lunarpine hadn't 
returned.  She was getting more and more worried about him.  She was 
about to go search for him if he didn't return soon.

She just had to know that he was alright and unharmed. If he came 
back all beat up and banged up, she would first get him back into 
health again and make sure he was alright.  Then she would let him 
have it.  She was mad at him for making her worry like this.  But 
really, she was concerned and hoped for is safe return.

She walked to the entrance and kept an eye out for him.
